article.headline: TCU scores first 16 points, but then falls to 2-3
article.linkText: Wisconsin-Green Bay rallies to knock off No. 25 TCU
article.story:
FORT WORTH, Texas (Ticker) -- Kristy Loiselle had 18 points 
and eight rebounds and Mary Kulenkamp buried a clutch 3-pointer
with 12 seconds left as Wisconsin-Green Bay rallied for a 60-58
victory over No. 25 Texas Christian.

TCU lost for the third time in four games despite
having double-digit leads in each half. TCU scored the first 16
points of the game, but had only a 29-27 lead at halftime.

Texas Christian led by as many as 11 in the second half but
Wisconsin-Green Bay (5-1) rallied to forge the game's first tie
at 55-55 on a jumper by Sara Boyer with 2:01 to go.

The Phoenix took their first lead 23 seconds later on a layup by
Chandra Johnson, who scored 16 points. Tiffany Evans made a
3-pointer for Texas Christian (2-3) at 26 seconds, but Kulenkamp
responded with her second 3-pointer of the game for the final
margin.

The Lady Frogs missed two shots on their final possession and
shot just 36 percent (20-for-55) for the game.

Candace Baldwin scored 16 points but was the only player in
double figures for Texas Christian.
